related_items.title: The price of Bolshevism in Finland
description: 6 photomechanical prints : halftone. | Six images relating to aftermath of battles in Helsinki, Finland during World War I and the Finnish Civil War. Images show a bombed tobacco factory, coffins of Germans, German machine gun carriages, German and White Guard troops, the residence of Baron Slanderskgold; and women giving cigarettes, chocolates, and flowers to German soldiers who cooperated with the White Guard in capturing Helsinki from the Bolshevik Red Guards.
